# Build context for docker/web/Dockerfile (context is the repo root: ../..).
# Denylist — anything not excluded here is sent to the daemon and may be COPYed.
# Keep it tight: a smaller context is faster to send and can't leak private trees.

# Dependencies + build artifacts — the image installs/builds its own.
node_modules
dist
web-dist

# Private trees — MUST NOT ship in the image.
deploy

# vendor/wirescope is deliberately INCLUDED (it is git-tracked; "unpublicized"
# means release notes, not the tree): the supervisor autostarts the proxy at
# engine boot when settings point at the managed local port (the default), so
# baking the snapshot in gives the container full wire telemetry. Its venv is
# built at first boot under CLODEX_DATA_DIR (persisted by the data volume).

# The other docker/ subdir is the peering test-box; neither belongs in the web
# image, and excluding docker/ keeps the context small (Dockerfile is read via -f,
# not from the context).
docker

# Not needed at build or runtime.
.git
.gitignore
.claude
peering
docs
test
# scripts/ is build/release tooling EXCEPT the two exec-intent helpers, which
# pot-bin.js materializes into ${CLODEX_BIN} at engine boot (the seeded
# exec-defs invoke `node "${CLODEX_BIN}/clodex-team.js"`). Excluding the whole
# dir shipped images where clodex-team/clodex-monitor execs were dead — so
# exclude the CONTENTS (`scripts/*`, not `scripts`: Docker cannot re-include
# children of an excluded directory) and negate the two runtime files back in.
scripts/*
!scripts/clodex-team.js
!scripts/clodex-monitor.js

# Scratch / local artifacts.
.DS_Store
*.local.md
*.log
HANDOFF.local.md
